data.description: Stunning Property with South Western Flare. Handsome log siding and Craftsman-style heavy beam construction have transformed this 1,658sf home into a neighborhood showpiece. The interior of the home reflects the owner's love of wood and artist's eye for color and drama. The lush kitchen counter is Silestone solid quartz and the cabinetry is made of Rustic Knotty Alder, as is all the framing and trim throughout the home, including the solid core doors. Manzanita touches in the living room add to the warm Native-American feel of the home. Sliding glass doors open to the Trex deck; a retractable awning responds to a handheld remote control to keep things cool on a sunny day. The home has three bedrooms and two full baths. The split-floorplan distances the master suite to the right wing of the home. Not only is there enough space for a king-size bed, there's also a cozy sitting area with French doors that open to a spectacular covered portion of the deck. The deck overlooks a beautiful private back yard, garden and small pasture area. From there you can follow a rustic path down a shaded bank to a peaceful spot by the creek - meditation bench included. There are fruit trees, evergreens, shrubs and flowers galore plus a spacious greenhouse and a garden shed.  The attached 2-car garage is finished. There's a large covered RVport. The entire home has a backup generator and a brand new 'old fashioned' hand pump that can draw from the well. Must see to  appreciate all the fine details making this stunning property so special.
